# PRIME v2 Developer Plan (mandatory)

After `git pull`, read and follow the plan **before** writing code.

## Entry points

1. [DEVELOPERS.md](../../DEVELOPERS.md) — human quick start
2. [docs/agents/AI-DEVELOPMENT-PLAN.md](../../docs/agents/AI-DEVELOPMENT-PLAN.md) — **AI canonical plan** (phase order, file map, gates)
3. [docs/agents/DEVELOPER-EXECUTION-PLAN.md](../../docs/agents/DEVELOPER-EXECUTION-PLAN.md) — detailed phase tasks
4. [docs/agents/TEST-MATRIX.md](../../docs/agents/TEST-MATRIX.md) — Pass/Fail per role and feature
5. [docs/agents/PHASES-REFERENCE.md](../../docs/agents/PHASES-REFERENCE.md) — current phase status

## Rules for AI assistants

- **Active phase:** 21A (test data + focal demo path). Check PHASES-REFERENCE before assuming.
- **Do not** implement RTEC, Budget, RD, PDF, staging, or production features until earlier phase gates pass.
- **Do not** skip TEST-MATRIX verification or QA-PUSH-GATE before push.
- State the active phase at the start of every implementation task.
- Only change files listed for the current phase in DEVELOPER-EXECUTION-PLAN.md unless the user explicitly expands scope.

## When user says "implement the plan"

1. Read AI-DEVELOPMENT-PLAN.md and DEVELOPER-EXECUTION-PLAN.md for the **current phase only**.
2. Implement that phase's tasks.
3. Run automated tests + mark TEST-MATRIX rows.
4. Update PHASES-REFERENCE when the phase gate closes.
5. Stop and report — do not continue to the next phase unless the user asks.
